race.comment: Pretty even heat of the spring series. EUGENIUS (1) is far better than recent form looks. Last start little went right and after facing pressure dropped right out. This is far easier and coming back in trip suits. Take catching off a better draw. SOLAR BLAST (9) turned in an eye-catching run last time and looks a big threat. Hit the line hard to just miss and although he will spot a start again has the claim and will motor late. HOOKED ON WEALTH (13) wasn't far away last time and the start prior in tougher company was placed in town. Wide gate to overcome but will be winding up late. OVERSTRIKE (5) is a former Hayes galloper resuming for a new yard. Has won fresh and off the low draw can give a sight. GRAND HOST (6) has been racing in tougher grade and looks well placed but has to overcome the tricky draw.
